What you need to know:

Held for more than five months, the impoverished migrants who originally escaped Ethiopia for a better life in Saudi Arabia are scraping by with barely enough food and water, the three said.Although the exact numbers of detainees is unknown, pictures have triggered global shock, shining a rare spotlight on tightly guarded Saudi detention centres that have long remained out of public view.Campaigners have called on Saudi Arabia to investigate allegations of the abusive and unsanitary conditions confronting migrants after some began talking to activists and international media using contraband cell phones.